36struct hb_bit_set_t
37{
38 hb_bit_set_t () = default;
39 ~hb_bit_set_t () = default;
40
41 hb_bit_set_t (const hb_bit_set_t& other) : hb_bit_set_t () { set (other, exact_size: true); }
42 hb_bit_set_t ( hb_bit_set_t&& other) : hb_bit_set_t () { hb_swap (*this, other); }
43 hb_bit_set_t& operator= (const hb_bit_set_t& other) { set (other); return *this; }
44 hb_bit_set_t& operator= (hb_bit_set_t&& other) { hb_swap (*this, other); return *this; }
45 friend void swap (hb_bit_set_t &a, hb_bit_set_t &b)
46 {
47 if (likely (!a.successful || !b.successful))
48 return;
49 hb_swap (a.population, b.population);
50 hb_swap (a.last_page_lookup, b.last_page_lookup);
51 hb_swap (a.page_map, b.page_map);
52 hb_swap (a.pages, b.pages);
53 }
54
55 void init ()
56 {
57 successful = true;
58 population = 0;
59 last_page_lookup = 0;
60 page_map.init ();
61 pages.init ();
62 }
63 void fini ()
64 {
65 page_map.fini ();
66 pages.fini ();
67 }

69 using page_t = hb_bit_page_t;
70 struct page_map_t
71 {
72 int cmp (const page_map_t &o) const { return cmp (o_major: o.major); }
73 int cmp (uint32_t o_major) const { return (int) o_major - (int) major; }
74
75 uint32_t major;
76 uint32_t index;
77 };
78
79 bool successful = true; /* Allocations successful */
80 mutable unsigned int population = 0;
81 mutable hb_atomic_int_t last_page_lookup = 0;
82 hb_sorted_vector_t<page_map_t> page_map;
83 hb_vector_t<page_t> pages;
84
85 void err () { if (successful) successful = false; } /* TODO Remove */
86 bool in_error () const { return !successful; }
87
88 bool resize (unsigned int count, bool clear = true, bool exact_size = false)
89 {
90 if (unlikely (!successful)) return false;
91
92 if (pages.length == 0 && count == 1)
93 exact_size = true; // Most sets are small and local
94
95 if (unlikely (!pages.resize (count, clear, exact_size) || !page_map.resize (count, clear, exact_size)))
96 {
97 pages.resize (size_: page_map.length, initialize: clear, exact: exact_size);
98 successful = false;
99 return false;
100 }
101 return true;
102 }
103
104 void alloc (unsigned sz)
105 {
106 sz >>= (page_t::PAGE_BITS_LOG_2 - 1);
107 pages.alloc (size: sz);
108 page_map.alloc (size: sz);
109 }
110
111 void reset ()
112 {
113 successful = true;
114 clear ();
115 }
116
117 void clear ()
118 {
119 resize (count: 0);
120 if (likely (successful))
121 population = 0;
122 }
123 bool is_empty () const
124 {
125 unsigned int count = pages.length;
126 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
127 if (!pages[i].is_empty ())
128 return false;
129 return true;
130 }
131 explicit operator bool () const { return !is_empty (); }
132
133 uint32_t hash () const
134 {
135 uint32_t h = 0;
136 for (auto &map : page_map)
137 h = h * 31 + hb_hash (map.major) + hb_hash (pages[map.index]);
138 return h;
139 }

141 private:
142 void dirty () { population = UINT_MAX; }

144
145 void add (hb_codepoint_t g)
146 {
147 if (unlikely (!successful)) return;
148 if (unlikely (g == INVALID)) return;
149 dirty ();
150 page_t *page = page_for (g, insert: true); if (unlikely (!page)) return;
151 page->add (g);
152 }
153 bool add_range (hb_codepoint_t a, hb_codepoint_t b)
154 {
155 if (unlikely (!successful)) return true; /* https://github.com/harfbuzz/harfbuzz/issues/657 */
156 if (unlikely (a > b || a == INVALID || b == INVALID)) return false;
157 dirty ();
158 unsigned int ma = get_major (g: a);
159 unsigned int mb = get_major (g: b);
160 if (ma == mb)
161 {
162 page_t *page = page_for (g: a, insert: true); if (unlikely (!page)) return false;
163 page->add_range (a, b);
164 }
165 else
166 {
167 page_t *page = page_for (g: a, insert: true); if (unlikely (!page)) return false;
168 page->add_range (a, b: major_start (major: ma + 1) - 1);
169
170 for (unsigned int m = ma + 1; m < mb; m++)
171 {
172 page = page_for (g: major_start (major: m), insert: true); if (unlikely (!page)) return false;
173 page->init1 ();
174 }
175
176 page = page_for (g: b, insert: true); if (unlikely (!page)) return false;
177 page->add_range (a: major_start (major: mb), b);
178 }
179 return true;
180 }

182 template <typename T>
183 void set_array (bool v, const T *array, unsigned int count, unsigned int stride=sizeof(T))
184 {
185 if (unlikely (!successful)) return;
186 if (!count) return;
187 dirty ();
188 hb_codepoint_t g = *array;
189 while (count)
190 {
191 unsigned int m = get_major (g);
192 page_t *page = page_for (g, insert: v); if (unlikely (v && !page)) return;
193 unsigned int start = major_start (major: m);
194 unsigned int end = major_start (major: m + 1);
195 do
196 {
197 if (v || page) /* The v check is to optimize out the page check if v is true. */
198 page->set (g, value: v);
199
200 array = &StructAtOffsetUnaligned<T> (array, stride);
201 count--;
202 }
203 while (count && (g = *array, start <= g && g < end));
204 }
205 }

213 template <typename T>

216 template <typename T>
217 void del_array (const hb_array_t<const T>& arr) { del_array (&arr, arr.len ()); }

219 /* Might return false if array looks unsorted.
220 * Used for faster rejection of corrupt data. */
221 template <typename T>
222 bool set_sorted_array (bool v, const T *array, unsigned int count, unsigned int stride=sizeof(T))
223 {
224 if (unlikely (!successful)) return true; /* https://github.com/harfbuzz/harfbuzz/issues/657 */
225 if (unlikely (!count)) return true;
226 dirty ();
227 hb_codepoint_t g = *array;
228 hb_codepoint_t last_g = g;
229 while (count)
230 {
231 unsigned int m = get_major (g);
232 page_t *page = page_for (g, insert: v); if (unlikely (v && !page)) return false;
233 unsigned int end = major_start (major: m + 1);
234 do
235 {
236 /* If we try harder we can change the following comparison to <=;
237 * Not sure if it's worth it. */
238 if (g < last_g) return false;
239 last_g = g;
240
241 if (v || page) /* The v check is to optimize out the page check if v is true. */
242 page->add (g);
243
244 array = &StructAtOffsetUnaligned<T> (array, stride);
245 count--;
246 }
247 while (count && (g = *array, g < end));
248 }
249 return true;
250 }

264 void del (hb_codepoint_t g)
265 {
266 if (unlikely (!successful)) return;
267 page_t *page = page_for (g);
268 if (!page)
269 return;
270 dirty ();
271 page->del (g);
272 }
273
274 private:
275 void del_pages (int ds, int de)
276 {
277 if (ds <= de)
278 {
279 // Pre-allocate the workspace that compact() will need so we can bail on allocation failure
280 // before attempting to rewrite the page map.
281 hb_vector_t<unsigned> compact_workspace;
282 if (unlikely (!allocate_compact_workspace (compact_workspace))) return;
283
284 unsigned int write_index = 0;
285 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < page_map.length; i++)
286 {
287 int m = (int) page_map[i].major;
288 if (m < ds || de < m)
289 page_map[write_index++] = page_map[i];
290 }
291 compact (workspace&: compact_workspace, length: write_index);
292 resize (count: write_index);
293 }
294 }
295
296
297 public:
298 void del_range (hb_codepoint_t a, hb_codepoint_t b)
299 {
300 if (unlikely (!successful)) return;
301 if (unlikely (a > b || a == INVALID)) return;
302 dirty ();
303 unsigned int ma = get_major (g: a);
304 unsigned int mb = get_major (g: b);
305 /* Delete pages from ds through de if ds <= de. */
306 int ds = (a == major_start (major: ma))? (int) ma: (int) (ma + 1);
307 int de = (b + 1 == major_start (major: mb + 1))? (int) mb: ((int) mb - 1);
308 if (ds > de || (int) ma < ds)
309 {
310 page_t *page = page_for (g: a);
311 if (page)
312 {
313 if (ma == mb)
314 page->del_range (a, b);
315 else
316 page->del_range (a, b: major_start (major: ma + 1) - 1);
317 }
318 }
319 if (de < (int) mb && ma != mb)
320 {
321 page_t *page = page_for (g: b);
322 if (page)
323 page->del_range (a: major_start (major: mb), b);
324 }
325 del_pages (ds, de);
326 }

332 return false;
333 return page->get (g);

348 bool intersects (hb_codepoint_t first, hb_codepoint_t last) const
349 {
350 hb_codepoint_t c = first - 1;
351 return next (codepoint: &c) && c <= last;

353 void set (const hb_bit_set_t &other, bool exact_size = false)
354 {
355 if (unlikely (!successful)) return;
356 unsigned int count = other.pages.length;
357 if (unlikely (!resize (count, false, exact_size)))
358 return;
359 population = other.population;
360
361 page_map = other.page_map;
362 pages = other.pages;
363 }
364
365 bool is_equal (const hb_bit_set_t &other) const
366 {
367 if (has_population () && other.has_population () &&
368 population != other.population)
369 return false;
370
371 unsigned int na = pages.length;
372 unsigned int nb = other.pages.length;
373
374 unsigned int a = 0, b = 0;
375 for (; a < na && b < nb; )
376 {
377 if (page_at (i: a).is_empty ()) { a++; continue; }
378 if (other.page_at (i: b).is_empty ()) { b++; continue; }
379 if (page_map[a].major != other.page_map[b].major ||
380 !page_at (i: a).is_equal (other: other.page_at (i: b)))
381 return false;
382 a++;
383 b++;
384 }
385 for (; a < na; a++)
386 if (!page_at (i: a).is_empty ()) { return false; }
387 for (; b < nb; b++)
388 if (!other.page_at (i: b).is_empty ()) { return false; }
389
390 return true;
391 }
392
393 bool is_subset (const hb_bit_set_t &larger_set) const
394 {
395 if (has_population () && larger_set.has_population () &&
396 population > larger_set.population)
397 return false;
398
399 uint32_t spi = 0;
400 for (uint32_t lpi = 0; spi < page_map.length && lpi < larger_set.page_map.length; lpi++)
401 {
402 uint32_t spm = page_map[spi].major;
403 uint32_t lpm = larger_set.page_map[lpi].major;
404 auto sp = page_at (i: spi);
405 auto lp = larger_set.page_at (i: lpi);
406
407 if (spm < lpm && !sp.is_empty ())
408 return false;
409
410 if (lpm < spm)
411 continue;
412
413 if (!sp.is_subset (larger_page: lp))
414 return false;
415
416 spi++;
417 }
418
419 while (spi < page_map.length)
420 if (!page_at (i: spi++).is_empty ())
421 return false;
422
423 return true;
424 }

426 private:
427 bool allocate_compact_workspace (hb_vector_t<unsigned>& workspace)
428 {
429 if (unlikely (!workspace.resize_exact (pages.length)))
430 {
431 successful = false;
432 return false;
433 }
434
435 return true;
436 }
437
438 /*
439 * workspace should be a pre-sized vector allocated to hold at exactly pages.length
440 * elements.
441 */
442 void compact (hb_vector_t<unsigned>& workspace,
443 unsigned int length)
444 {
445 assert(workspace.length == pages.length);
446 hb_vector_t<unsigned>& old_index_to_page_map_index = workspace;
447
448 hb_fill (c: old_index_to_page_map_index.writer(), v: 0xFFFFFFFF);
449 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; i++)
450 old_index_to_page_map_index[page_map[i].index] = i;
451
452 compact_pages (old_index_to_page_map_index);
453 }
454 void compact_pages (const hb_vector_t<unsigned>& old_index_to_page_map_index)
455 {
456 unsigned int write_index = 0;
457 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < pages.length; i++)
458 {
459 if (old_index_to_page_map_index[i] == 0xFFFFFFFF) continue;
460
461 if (write_index < i)
462 pages[write_index] = pages[i];
463
464 page_map[old_index_to_page_map_index[i]].index = write_index;
465 write_index++;
466 }
467 }
468 public:
469
470 void process_ (hb_bit_page_t::vector_t (*op) (const hb_bit_page_t::vector_t &, const hb_bit_page_t::vector_t &),
471 bool passthru_left, bool passthru_right,
472 const hb_bit_set_t &other)
473 {
474 if (unlikely (!successful)) return;
475
476 dirty ();
477
478 unsigned int na = pages.length;
479 unsigned int nb = other.pages.length;
480 unsigned int next_page = na;
481
482 unsigned int count = 0, newCount = 0;
483 unsigned int a = 0, b = 0;
484 unsigned int write_index = 0;
485
486 // Pre-allocate the workspace that compact() will need so we can bail on allocation failure
487 // before attempting to rewrite the page map.
488 hb_vector_t<unsigned> compact_workspace;
489 if (!passthru_left && unlikely (!allocate_compact_workspace (compact_workspace))) return;
490
491 for (; a < na && b < nb; )
492 {
493 if (page_map[a].major == other.page_map[b].major)
494 {
495 if (!passthru_left)
496 {
497 // Move page_map entries that we're keeping from the left side set
498 // to the front of the page_map vector. This isn't necessary if
499 // passthru_left is set since no left side pages will be removed
500 // in that case.
501 if (write_index < a)
502 page_map[write_index] = page_map[a];
503 write_index++;
504 }
505
506 count++;
507 a++;
508 b++;
509 }
510 else if (page_map[a].major < other.page_map[b].major)
511 {
512 if (passthru_left)
513 count++;
514 a++;
515 }
516 else
517 {
518 if (passthru_right)
519 count++;
520 b++;
521 }
522 }
523 if (passthru_left)
524 count += na - a;
525 if (passthru_right)
526 count += nb - b;
527
528 if (!passthru_left)
529 {
530 na = write_index;
531 next_page = write_index;
532 compact (workspace&: compact_workspace, length: write_index);
533 }
534
535 if (unlikely (!resize (count)))
536 return;
537
538 newCount = count;
539
540 /* Process in-place backward. */
541 a = na;
542 b = nb;
543 for (; a && b; )
544 {
545 if (page_map.arrayZ[a - 1].major == other.page_map.arrayZ[b - 1].major)
546 {
547 a--;
548 b--;
549 count--;
550 page_map.arrayZ[count] = page_map.arrayZ[a];
551 page_at (i: count).v = op (page_at (i: a).v, other.page_at (i: b).v);
552 }
553 else if (page_map.arrayZ[a - 1].major > other.page_map.arrayZ[b - 1].major)
554 {
555 a--;
556 if (passthru_left)
557 {
558 count--;
559 page_map.arrayZ[count] = page_map.arrayZ[a];
560 }
561 }
562 else
563 {
564 b--;
565 if (passthru_right)
566 {
567 count--;
568 page_map.arrayZ[count].major = other.page_map.arrayZ[b].major;
569 page_map.arrayZ[count].index = next_page++;
570 page_at (i: count).v = other.page_at (i: b).v;
571 }
572 }
573 }
574 if (passthru_left)
575 while (a)
576 {
577 a--;
578 count--;
579 page_map.arrayZ[count] = page_map.arrayZ[a];
580 }
581 if (passthru_right)
582 while (b)
583 {
584 b--;
585 count--;
586 page_map.arrayZ[count].major = other.page_map.arrayZ[b].major;
587 page_map.arrayZ[count].index = next_page++;
588 page_at (i: count).v = other.page_at (i: b).v;
589 }
590 assert (!count);
591 resize (count: newCount);
592 }
593 template <typename Op>
594 static hb_bit_page_t::vector_t
595 op_ (const hb_bit_page_t::vector_t &a, const hb_bit_page_t::vector_t &b)
596 { return Op{} (a, b); }
597 template <typename Op>
598 void process (const Op& op, const hb_bit_set_t &other)
599 {
600 process_ (op: op_<Op>, passthru_left: op (1, 0), passthru_right: op (0, 1), other);
601 }
602
603 void union_ (const hb_bit_set_t &other) { process (op: hb_bitwise_or, other); }
604 void intersect (const hb_bit_set_t &other) { process (op: hb_bitwise_and, other); }
605 void subtract (const hb_bit_set_t &other) { process (op: hb_bitwise_gt, other); }
606 void symmetric_difference (const hb_bit_set_t &other) { process (op: hb_bitwise_xor, other); }
607
608 bool next (hb_codepoint_t *codepoint) const
609 {
610 if (unlikely (*codepoint == INVALID)) {
611 *codepoint = get_min ();
612 return *codepoint != INVALID;
613 }
614
615 const auto* page_map_array = page_map.arrayZ;
616 unsigned int major = get_major (g: *codepoint);
617 unsigned int i = last_page_lookup;
618
619 if (unlikely (i >= page_map.length || page_map_array[i].major != major))
620 {
621 page_map.bfind (x: major, i: &i, not_found: HB_NOT_FOUND_STORE_CLOSEST);
622 if (i >= page_map.length) {
623 *codepoint = INVALID;
624 return false;
625 }
626 }
627
628 const auto* pages_array = pages.arrayZ;
629 const page_map_t &current = page_map_array[i];
630 if (likely (current.major == major))
631 {
632 if (pages_array[current.index].next (codepoint))
633 {
634 *codepoint += current.major * page_t::PAGE_BITS;
635 last_page_lookup = i;
636 return true;
637 }
638 i++;
639 }
640
641 for (; i < page_map.length; i++)
642 {
643 const page_map_t &current = page_map_array[i];
644 hb_codepoint_t m = pages_array[current.index].get_min ();
645 if (m != INVALID)
646 {
647 *codepoint = current.major * page_t::PAGE_BITS + m;
648 last_page_lookup = i;
649 return true;
650 }
651 }
652 last_page_lookup = 0;
653 *codepoint = INVALID;
654 return false;
655 }
656 bool previous (hb_codepoint_t *codepoint) const
657 {
658 if (unlikely (*codepoint == INVALID)) {
659 *codepoint = get_max ();
660 return *codepoint != INVALID;
661 }
662
663 page_map_t map = {.major: get_major (g: *codepoint), .index: 0};
664 unsigned int i;
665 page_map.bfind (x: map, i: &i, not_found: HB_NOT_FOUND_STORE_CLOSEST);
666 if (i < page_map.length && page_map.arrayZ[i].major == map.major)
667 {
668 if (pages[page_map.arrayZ[i].index].previous (codepoint))
669 {
670 *codepoint += page_map.arrayZ[i].major * page_t::PAGE_BITS;
671 return true;
672 }
673 }
674 i--;
675 for (; (int) i >= 0; i--)
676 {
677 hb_codepoint_t m = pages.arrayZ[page_map.arrayZ[i].index].get_max ();
678 if (m != INVALID)
679 {
680 *codepoint = page_map.arrayZ[i].major * page_t::PAGE_BITS + m;
681 return true;
682 }
683 }
684 *codepoint = INVALID;
685 return false;
686 }
687 bool next_range (hb_codepoint_t *first, hb_codepoint_t *last) const
688 {
689 hb_codepoint_t i;
690
691 i = *last;
692 if (!next (codepoint: &i))
693 {
694 *last = *first = INVALID;
695 return false;
696 }
697
698 /* TODO Speed up. */
699 *last = *first = i;
700 while (next (codepoint: &i) && i == *last + 1)
701 (*last)++;
702
703 return true;
704 }
705 bool previous_range (hb_codepoint_t *first, hb_codepoint_t *last) const
706 {
707 hb_codepoint_t i;
708
709 i = *first;
710 if (!previous (codepoint: &i))
711 {
712 *last = *first = INVALID;
713 return false;
714 }
715
716 /* TODO Speed up. */
717 *last = *first = i;
718 while (previous (codepoint: &i) && i == *first - 1)
719 (*first)--;
720
721 return true;
722 }

724 unsigned int next_many (hb_codepoint_t codepoint,
725 hb_codepoint_t *out,
726 unsigned int size) const
727 {
728 // By default, start at the first bit of the first page of values.
729 unsigned int start_page = 0;
730 unsigned int start_page_value = 0;
731 if (unlikely (codepoint != INVALID))
732 {
733 const auto* page_map_array = page_map.arrayZ;
734 unsigned int major = get_major (g: codepoint);
735 unsigned int i = last_page_lookup;
736 if (unlikely (i >= page_map.length || page_map_array[i].major != major))
737 {
738 page_map.bfind (x: major, i: &i, not_found: HB_NOT_FOUND_STORE_CLOSEST);
739 if (i >= page_map.length)
740 return 0; // codepoint is greater than our max element.
741 }
742 start_page = i;
743 start_page_value = page_remainder (g: codepoint + 1);
744 if (unlikely (start_page_value == 0))
745 {
746 // The export-after value was last in the page. Start on next page.
747 start_page++;
748 start_page_value = 0;
749 }
750 }
751
752 unsigned int initial_size = size;
753 for (unsigned int i = start_page; i < page_map.length && size; i++)
754 {
755 uint32_t base = major_start (major: page_map[i].major);
756 unsigned int n = pages[page_map[i].index].write (base, start_value: start_page_value, p: out, size);
757 out += n;
758 size -= n;
759 start_page_value = 0;
760 }
761 return initial_size - size;
762 }
763
764 unsigned int next_many_inverted (hb_codepoint_t codepoint,
765 hb_codepoint_t *out,
766 unsigned int size) const
767 {
768 unsigned int initial_size = size;
769 // By default, start at the first bit of the first page of values.
770 unsigned int start_page = 0;
771 unsigned int start_page_value = 0;
772 if (unlikely (codepoint != INVALID))
773 {
774 const auto* page_map_array = page_map.arrayZ;
775 unsigned int major = get_major (g: codepoint);
776 unsigned int i = last_page_lookup;
777 if (unlikely (i >= page_map.length || page_map_array[i].major != major))
778 {
779 page_map.bfind(x: major, i: &i, not_found: HB_NOT_FOUND_STORE_CLOSEST);
780 if (unlikely (i >= page_map.length))
781 {
782 // codepoint is greater than our max element.
783 while (++codepoint != INVALID && size)
784 {
785 *out++ = codepoint;
786 size--;
787 }
788 return initial_size - size;
789 }
790 }
791 start_page = i;
792 start_page_value = page_remainder (g: codepoint + 1);
793 if (unlikely (start_page_value == 0))
794 {
795 // The export-after value was last in the page. Start on next page.
796 start_page++;
797 start_page_value = 0;
798 }
799 }
800
801 hb_codepoint_t next_value = codepoint + 1;
802 for (unsigned int i=start_page; i<page_map.length && size; i++)
803 {
804 uint32_t base = major_start (major: page_map[i].major);
805 unsigned int n = pages[page_map[i].index].write_inverted (base, start_value: start_page_value, p: out, size, next_value: &next_value);
806 out += n;
807 size -= n;
808 start_page_value = 0;
809 }
810 while (next_value < HB_SET_VALUE_INVALID && size) {
811 *out++ = next_value++;
812 size--;
813 }
814 return initial_size - size;
815 }

817 bool has_population () const { return population != UINT_MAX; }
818 unsigned int get_population () const
819 {
820 if (has_population ())
821 return population;
822
823 unsigned int pop = 0;
824 unsigned int count = pages.length;
825 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
826 pop += pages[i].get_population ();
827
828 population = pop;
829 return pop;
830 }
831 hb_codepoint_t get_min () const
832 {
833 unsigned count = pages.length;
834 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; i++)
835 {
836 const auto& map = page_map[i];
837 const auto& page = pages[map.index];
838
839 if (!page.is_empty ())
840 return map.major * page_t::PAGE_BITS + page.get_min ();
841 }
842 return INVALID;
843 }
844 hb_codepoint_t get_max () const
845 {
846 unsigned count = pages.length;
847 for (signed i = count - 1; i >= 0; i--)
848 {
849 const auto& map = page_map[(unsigned) i];
850 const auto& page = pages[map.index];
851
852 if (!page.is_empty ())
853 return map.major * page_t::PAGE_BITS + page.get_max ();
854 }
855 return INVALID;
856 }

863 struct iter_t : hb_iter_with_fallback_t<iter_t, hb_codepoint_t>
864 {
865 static constexpr bool is_sorted_iterator = true;
866 iter_t (const hb_bit_set_t &s_ = Null (hb_bit_set_t),
867 bool init = true) : s (&s_), v (INVALID), l(0)
868 {
869 if (init)
870 {
871 l = s->get_population () + 1;
872 __next__ ();
873 }
874 }
875
876 typedef hb_codepoint_t __item_t__;
877 hb_codepoint_t __item__ () const { return v; }
878 bool __more__ () const { return v != INVALID; }
879 void __next__ () { s->next (codepoint: &v); if (l) l--; }
880 void __prev__ () { s->previous (codepoint: &v); }
881 unsigned __len__ () const { return l; }
882 iter_t end () const { return iter_t (*s, false); }
883 bool operator != (const iter_t& o) const
884 { return s != o.s || v != o.v; }
885
886 protected:
887 const hb_bit_set_t *s;
888 hb_codepoint_t v;
889 unsigned l;
890 };
891 iter_t iter () const { return iter_t (*this); }
892 operator iter_t () const { return iter (); }

896 page_t *page_for (hb_codepoint_t g, bool insert = false)
897 {
898 unsigned major = get_major (g);
899
900 /* The extra page_map length is necessary; can't just rely on vector here,
901 * since the next check would be tricked because a null page also has
902 * major==0, which we can't distinguish from an actualy major==0 page... */
903 unsigned i = last_page_lookup;
904 if (likely (i < page_map.length))
905 {
906 auto &cached_page = page_map.arrayZ[i];
907 if (cached_page.major == major)
908 return &pages.arrayZ[cached_page.index];
909 }
910
911 page_map_t map = {.major: major, .index: pages.length};
912 if (!page_map.bfind (x: map, i: &i, not_found: HB_NOT_FOUND_STORE_CLOSEST))
913 {
914 if (!insert)
915 return nullptr;
916
917 if (unlikely (!resize (pages.length + 1)))
918 return nullptr;
919
920 pages.arrayZ[map.index].init0 ();
921 memmove (dest: page_map.arrayZ + i + 1,
922 src: page_map.arrayZ + i,
923 n: (page_map.length - 1 - i) * page_map.item_size);
924 page_map[i] = map;
925 }
926
927 last_page_lookup = i;
928 return &pages.arrayZ[page_map.arrayZ[i].index];
929 }
930 const page_t *page_for (hb_codepoint_t g) const
931 {
932 unsigned major = get_major (g);
933
934 /* The extra page_map length is necessary; can't just rely on vector here,
935 * since the next check would be tricked because a null page also has
936 * major==0, which we can't distinguish from an actualy major==0 page... */
937 unsigned i = last_page_lookup;
938 if (likely (i < page_map.length))
939 {
940 auto &cached_page = page_map.arrayZ[i];
941 if (cached_page.major == major)
942 return &pages.arrayZ[cached_page.index];
943 }
944
945 page_map_t key = {.major: major};
946 if (!page_map.bfind (x: key, i: &i))
947 return nullptr;
948
949 last_page_lookup = i;
950 return &pages.arrayZ[page_map[i].index];
951 }
952 page_t &page_at (unsigned int i)
953 {
954 assert (i < page_map.length);
955 return pages.arrayZ[page_map.arrayZ[i].index];
956 }
957 const page_t &page_at (unsigned int i) const
958 {
959 assert (i < page_map.length);
960 return pages.arrayZ[page_map.arrayZ[i].index];
961 }
962 unsigned int get_major (hb_codepoint_t g) const { return g >> page_t::PAGE_BITS_LOG_2; }
963 unsigned int page_remainder (hb_codepoint_t g) const { return g & page_t::PAGE_BITMASK; }
964 hb_codepoint_t major_start (unsigned int major) const { return major << page_t::PAGE_BITS_LOG_2; }
965};
